children.subject: 120 is webcast if you want to take both

history.content:
Profs. Ayazifar and Ranade are both wonderful lecturers, and both classes are foundational, so the decision of which to take sooner can probably be made primarily by looking at which one is a requirement for more of the courses you want to take later on. If you're interested in taking 189 in the fall, take 127 this semester. If you're interested in taking 226A in the fall, you'll have to take 120 this semester. The most natural successor to 120 is 123, which is generally only offered in the spring, so if that's your plan, you can take 120 in the fall and 127 this semester.

Some other differences: 120 has ~6 homeworks while 127 has ~12; 120 usually doesn't have a final with Prof. Ayazifar, while 127 will.

As someone mentioned below, 120 will probably be webcast, but it's worth noting that both classes have historically had in-class exams, which may cause trouble if exam dates coincide. Odds are that you can pull off taking both classes though.

I noticed there are still some open spots in EECS127 and I was thinking about swapping Math 110 for it, but EECS127 lectures conflict with EE120 lectures. Both 120 and 127 seem pretty useful for ML, robotics, or EECS things more generally and both profs also have good reviews on HKN for those classes. Any recommendations on which class would be better to take now rather than in the future?
